This paper is about channel modeling and simulation for millimeter-wave communication systems, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on modeling and simulating the channel coefficients for wideband communication systems. The second most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper discusses the use of electrically-steerable and narrow beam antenna arrays, which are important for wireless networking. The third most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as millimeter-wave communication systems are often used for high-bandwidth multimedia applications. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), as the paper discusses the implementation of the channel simulator. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the use of a Markov model to simulate dynamic human blockage shadowing loss.
